<br>
There was once a bug in which Rains could potentially poof a corpse if it killed the mob, similar to the old problem of DoTs with an absent caster. Rains, after all, deliver damage after the casting is complete, it is certainly not inconceivable that if the Mage was killed while the Rain was falling (or hahahahaha by the Rain itself!) that successive rains could cause a poofing problem.<br>
<br>
Enter code to lock Rains from hurting a mob under 10% of its life.<br>
<br>
Some time ago SOE (or was it VI then?) makes a claim that this is now fixed, and that Rains can once again kill mobs. Some protectionist code is removed, but due to the nature of the game engine, underlying code remains and in almost all cases Rains can stil not kill mobs.<br>
<br>
Actually, I am willing to bet my Orb that what's happened is that they have removed the &quot;kill check&quot; portion of the problem, and the sneakier (probably undocumented) &quot;10% check&quot; remains. <br>
<br>
Tell me you can't see a Dev walking up to Orc 3 in EC, casting a Rain on the camp, watching them die and going &quot;Cool, all fixed&quot;? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><CENTER><table width=500 border=0 cellspacing=4>
