<br>
I don't know whether this was done to represent the mobs last ditch efforts to save themselves, or simply playing on the tunnel vision of players....but I've lost count of how many times I've died to mobs at the 0 to 2% mark....<br>
<br>
I'm willing to bet on the tunnel vision hypothesis...Sony is interested in keeping people playing EQ for a long long time (forever?) One of the ways they accomplish this is penalty (exp loss or death tax.) When a mob gets low, the players attention becomes more visceral (tunnel vision), less rational. When this happens the player is much less likely to run, thinking &quot;I can finish this kill&quot;. With a mob's resistance increased at this point, the normal flow of damage (via DD spell) changes...the mob survives, and more player deaths result.<br>
<br>
One more nuke should finish him...damn resisted....pet down, I'm oom....Run!....LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<br>
<br>
Understanding the psychology doesn't make you immune to its effects....<br>
<br>
.02<br>
<br>
