<br>
seriously, test the 10% rule if you don't believe it.  get a mob that runs and knock it down to 8% or so and rain it, you won't get a single hit till it regens to 10 or 11, as soon as it does you'll get a hit.  i did this specifically to test this a while back, so unless they changed it in like the last month or 2 it's still coded for 10%.  a rain can kill, but only if it hits at &gt;10% and takes the mob to zero hp in one hit from there.<br>
<br>
edit: had an idea<br>
it's probably psycholgical, you don't usually nuke at 10% unless it's an emergency.  and if it does resist then you die.  therefore the low-hp resists seem to stand out more than other resists that would go unnoticed. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fabbz>Fabbz</A> at: 3/4/03 7:02:46 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral>General</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
